How to put into words, or a 60 second video clip, this extraordinary loss; an end to more than 14 years with my Gracie. My beautiful, precocious, stealth-mode, spinning baby puffin. You have made life better all this time. People have said “oh she’s one of your dogs-right?” No, she was my baby; my family. And even though she was  known for being silent, today the house is eerily quiet, proving how a being can fill a space just with their energy. It’s never easy to lose someone you love; but this one hits a little harder. 🙏🏽

Today we not only celebrate the life of this man, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., we turn to his words. His ethos of choosing love over hate, of not sitting idly by and watching things being done that offend the connection that God placed between all of us, the idea that doing for others is a privilege, the requirement for equality for all mankind as well as kindness to all living beings, and the willingness to sacrifice for all of these things…we need to embody these ideals TODAY. We have been manipulated and separated from one another and from God and only by standing for what is right, standing for each other, and standing against those who would break us apart and control us will we see our way through. The spirit of Dr King lives on. Today and every day.

KMDxBG:  a 15 year love affair

Today marks my 15 year anniversary with  iconic @bergdorfs 

It was January 28, 2008 that my collection first debuted in a small pod in the fine jewelry department at Bergdorf Goodman.  Bergdorf was actually the first store to call me about my collection. 
I have made some wonderful  lifelong friends thanks to this partnership. I am thankful to every single person who believed in me. Every person who gave me a chance with my cool stones and organic vibe. I am proud to be part of the Bergdorf family and look forward to the next 15 years and all of the great fun and exciting experiences to come.

This clip is a little throw back to my BG special residency last year ✨

A strong woman stands up for herself. A stronger woman stands up for those who cannot stand up for themselves. There are no limit to what we , as women, can accomplish. Make every step count and be strong mentally, physically, and spiritually; while maintaining a sensitivity and femininity that embodies femininity. Remember…we have the power to bring about change in this world. 
When we support each other, incredible things happen. March 8 is a special date to show that united we are stronger , that every day our voice sounds louder, and that we want to live in a society free of fear. Today, lets not just celebrate the women who have succeeded , but also the ones who are still fighting for their place in this world. And always those who sacrificed before us for the rights of women around the world. 
Much love,
KMD

As citizens of the world, it is every person’s responsibility to nurture and preserve the bountiful gifts of nature, its resources, the environment and the atmosphere. A pledge, no matter how small it is, taken in this direction will go a long way in the betterment of Mother Earth, making it a better place to live in for generations to come.

Each year millions of animals, specifically dogs, are abandoned by their owners at shelters across the country. Most people are unaware that after 3 days any dog or cat left at the shelter is up for euthanization at the discretion of the shelter director. As a result, on average 1.5 million shelter animals are euthanized in the United States each year. That’s around 670 000 dogs and 860 000 cats annually. This country needs to move towards a moratorium on backyard breeding and strict legislation against animal abuse and neglect. More importantly, there needs to be legislation making The United States a no kill nation. 
Today honors the inspiring ways rescue dogs become a part of the human family. The day also increases awareness about the number of dogs in shelters. Given a chance, they fill their forever homes with unconditional love and unlimited joy. #RescueDontShop #adoptdontshop

Taking into consideration all of that and much, much more, what’s not to love about elephants? Still, countless elephants are brutally killed every year for their ivory by greedy poachers who then leave their carcasses to rot in the sun. As Graydon Carter, Editor of Vanity Fair put it:
We admire elephants in part because they demonstrate what we consider the finest human traits, but the way we treat them puts on display the very worst of human behavior.

World Elephant Day is an international annual event on August 12, dedicated to the preservation and protection of the world's elephants and it’s the perfect time to find out more about these amazing animals and what we can do to preserve and protect them.

Thanksgiving 2023. 
Give Thanks. Not just today but every day. In a world that is increasingly chaotic and unstable, take today to recognize the people in your life for which you are thankful for. Take today to think about the small things that maybe you take for granted in your  day-to-day life, but for which you are thankful for.  As we look around the world and see so many in need and in so much pain, let’s be grateful for all we have. 

“Thanksgiving”  has two elements. Yes the Thanks part but let’s not forget the Giving part.  Be Thankful that you are able to Give. And make this the year we all give generously to those in need.  Sometimes as we rush through life trying to manage our own situations we can forget that when we stop and think of others, give to others, we fulfill our purpose as humans. I’m giving, we receive. 

And finally, personally, I am thankful to everyone who has supported and believed in me thru thick and thin. It doesn’t go unnoticed.  For those few of you, you already know I got you. Always. 

Happy Thanksgiving!
KMD
